arngc (20140708) wtf; urgency=low

  * make “arngc stop” kill arngc-slrd as well
  * use TCP keepalives on the Linux side, kill hanging conns after 60s

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Tue, 08 Jul 2014 14:58:06 +0200

arngc (20140704) wtf; urgency=low

  * add arngb-slrd.c example, transfer MirBSD<->MirBSD using SSH
  * do not use fd for stunnel4 to avoid zombies hanging around
  * modernise
  * conflict with rngd from The Distribution which cannot be named
    since they switched away from Debian’s codebase to upstream’s
    (which lacks required features)
  * force gzip compression
  * fix operation with stunnel 5.x (and up to 9.x if they keep compatible)

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Fri, 04 Jul 2014 22:00:38 +0000

arngc (20131024) unstable; urgency=low

  * revert changes from 20131023 that were not the cause of the issue
  * implement the back direction, fixing that by making stdin live

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Thu, 24 Oct 2013 11:32:00 +0200

arngc (20131023) unstable; urgency=low

  * work around OpenSSL doing 0/n ipv 1/n-1 split

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Wed, 23 Oct 2013 21:25:23 +0000

arngc (20130222) unstable; urgency=low

  * fix start on slow systems (eg. busy m68k buildd)
  * document missing IP support, only Legacy IP works

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Fri, 22 Feb 2013 12:47:39 +0000

arngc (20120509) unstable; urgency=low

  * README.Debian: mention how to disable stunnel, too
  * clean up; mark as Multi-Arch; bump Policy
  * if stunnel4, avoid zombies, drive it directly instead of
    using the stunnel 3 compat wrapper
  * do not pollute the process list that much

 -- Thorsten Glaser <tg@@mirbsd.de>  Wed, 09 May 2012 11:09:38 +0000

arngc (20110804) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial Release

